quran[22]{c,v,t,f}:
  54,28,"and tell them that the water is to be shared between them<sup>10</sup>; each should take its drink in turn.","[10] i.e., one day for the tribe of Thamūd and one day for the she-camel."
  54,29,"But they called their companion<sup>11</sup>, and he undertook the task<sup>12</sup> and hamstrung her.","[11] i.e., the worst among them.\n [12] Or took his sword."
  54,30,"Then how [terrible] My punishment and My warnings were!",""
  54,31,"We sent against them a single blast, leaving them like trampled hedge-building twigs<sup>13</sup>.","[13] The people of Thamūd were crushed like trampled and trodden twigs and pieces of bush lying around an enclosure for cattle."
  54,32,"We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed?",""
  54,33,"The people of Lot rejected the warnings.",""
  54,34,"We sent against them a storm of pebbles, except the family of Lot whom We saved before dawn,",""
  54,35,"as a blessing from Us. Thus do We reward those who give thanks.",""
  54,36,"He had already warned them of Our punishing assault, but they doubted the warnings.",""
  54,37,"They even demanded that he let them have their way with his angel-guests<sup>14</sup>, so We blinded their eyes, [saying], “Taste My punishment and My warnings!”","[14] Whom Allah sent in the form of handsome young men."
  54,38,"By the early morning a lasting torment overtook them.",""
  54,39,"Taste My punishment and My warnings!",""
  54,40,"We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed?",""
  54,41,"Indeed, warnings came to the people of Pharaoh.",""
  54,42,"But they rejected all of Our signs, so We seized them with the grip of the All-Mighty, Most Powerful.",""
  54,43,"Are your disbelievers [O Makkans] superior to those<sup>15</sup> or have you been granted immunity in divine Scriptures?","[15] i.e., those destroyed peoples."
  54,44,"Or do they say, “We are a united front, bound to prevail.”?",""
  54,45,"Soon their united front will be defeated, and they will flee<sup>16</sup>.","[16] This foretold event was fulfilled in the Battle of Badr."
  54,46,"But the Hour is their appointed time, and the Hour is more catastrophic and more bitter.",""
  54,47,"Indeed, the wicked are in error and madness<sup>17</sup>.","[17] Or ""in the blazes of fire."""
  54,48,"On the Day when they will be dragged into the Fire on their faces, [they will be told], “Taste the agony of Hell<sup>18</sup>!”","[18] ""Saqar"" is one of the names of Hell."
  54,49,"We have surely created everything in a determined measure<sup>19</sup>.","[19] Or perfectly preordained."
